FBIS4-36111 "drnes109_p_94002" FBIS-NES-94-109 Daily Report 6 Jun 1994 Afghanistan Explosion in Mazar-e Sharif Kills Militia Members Explosion in Mazar-e Sharif Kills Militia Members LD0606172294 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 GMT 6 Jun 94 LD0606172294 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network Pashto BFN [Text] Reports from reliable security sources say that last Saturday [4 June], a huge explosion took place in the Huzori Bagh, a five-story building in Mazar-e Sharif, in which at the present the so-called Central Office of Jenbish [National Islamic Movement of North, led by Dostam] is located. As a result of this explosion a number of militiamen were killed and the building was damaged. Eye-witnesses say that the number of such explosion has recently increased, which indicates chaos in the militias security systems.
